post_title: 6th Annual Poker Run for the Haley House
post_content: The Riverview Detachment of the Marine Corps League #1226 and the American Legion Riders Post #148 will be conducting their 6th annual Poker Run October 27, 2012. The event is open to the public and the proceeds will benefit the Haley House which provides a temporary home to the family members of Wounded Warriors and Veterans who are in the Spinal Cord, Traumatic Brain and Blast Injury Treatment Center at the James Haley VA Hospital. The Haley House receives no funding from any government entity; only private donations. They take any family members of wounded warriors that are 50 miles or over from home and are suffering with financial constraints.Poker run, 50/50, raffles.Registration opens at 9 am.KSU at 10:30 am.

post_content: Saturday, November 10 and Sunday, November 1110 am–6 pm •      Free Museum entry for Military and their families*Free entry with valid Military ID for 1 additional adult and up to 4 children 18 years old or younger. •       Special Museum Lobby DisplayThe 2011 & 2012 Custom Bike Show People’s Choice award winner “Tribute Bike,” owned by Vietnam Vet Lee McAndrew, will be on display in the museum lobby. The bike features various scenes related to the Vietnam War and tributes to specific individuals who served. •       American Flag CollectionBring your worn American flag to the museum to be properly retired.  •       Harley-Davidson Flag SigningSign a Harley-Davidson flag to be presented to a military unit serving overseas. 11 am–3 pm•        Live American Bald Eagle on Display      Glory, the museum’s feathered ambassador, will be on-site. Interact, learn and get your photo taken with Glory in the museum’s Experience Gallery.  Saturday, November 10 only2 pm•        St. John’s Northwestern Military Academy ProgramSt. John’s Northwestern Military Academy will perform a ceremony to honor six branches of war veterans from World War I to current conflicts. Program will conclude with a 21-gun salute. 3 pm•       St. John’s Northwestern Military Drill TeamThe St. John’s Northwestern Military Academy “Silver Rifles” Exhibition Drill Team will perform intricate precision marching, and demilitarized rifle spinning and tossing.
print_desc: Harley-Davidson has a long history of supporting the military, and the Harley-Davidson Museum has many free and family-friendly events happening November 10–11, 2012. Activities include performances by the St. John's Military Academy, a special Military-dedicated lobby display, and free Museum entry for Military and their families*. *Free entry with valid Military ID for 1 additional adult and up to 4 children 18 years old or younger.
reg_desc: *Free entry with valid Military ID for 1 additional adult and up to 4 children 18 years old or younger.

post_title: United Motorcycle Clubs of Alameda County 2012 Toy Drive
post_content: United Motorcycle Clubs of Alameda CountyUMCoAC, a collective of more than 50 local motorcycle clubs, volunteers each year to help find sponsors for LOV’s Adopt-A-Family program and organizes a toy drive and motorcycle run, providing all the donated toys and all collected proceeds to LOV.This event takes place across three locations.1) Start Point: Big Mommas Upholstery, 1980 American Ave. Hayward, CA 94545Registration: 10 amLeaving: 12 pm Noon2) LOV Meet and Greet Location: 36120 Ruschin Dr, Newark, CA 94560Arrive ~ 30 minutes, Duration with kids: ~ 3 hours3) End Point for run and event: Oakland Moose Lodge Hall, 690 Hegenberger Road, Oakland. post_title: Dixie ABATE of Alabama 2nd Ride to the Capitol
post_content: On Saturday, April 20, 2013, Dixie ABATE will sponsor our 2nd "Ride for Rights and Motorist Awareness", a police-escorted ride to the state capitol in Montgomery to promote safety and awareness and to kick off “Motorcycle Safety Month,” which has historically been the month of May. Staging Area: the Walmart Shopping Center at 6545 Atlanta Highway, MontgomeryDeparture: at 12:00 pm sharp. Bikes should be in place and ready to roll by 11:30 am. It is a short 7 mile ride from there to the capitol.We need your support. Plan now to join us. This will be a proud moment for Dixie ABATE, and we expect coverage by the news media. Groups of riders from all over the state will unite and converge on the state capitol building in Montgomery to draw motorists' attention to the presence of motorcycles on our highways and to let Alabama's lawmakers know the motorcyclists in Alabama now have a strong voice. Don’t miss out on what looks to be the most historic gathering of motorcycles ever in Alabama!For up-to-date information on this event, check the event folder on our forum, e-mail kcook@dixieabate.org, or call Kris Cook at 205.617.9944. To learn more about Dixie ABATE and to see how you can become a member, go to www.dixieabate.org.Please go to www.dixieabate.org and register and let us know how many will be coming with you on this ride. We need a head count. You don't want to miss out on this event, it's going to be HUGE! This is your chance to make a statement. There's POWER in numbers and we need numbers. Dixie ABATE is here for YOU so come out and bring your friends and show your support. Thanks!
print_desc: police-escorted ride to the state capitol in Montgomery to promote safety and awareness and to kick off “Motorcycle Safety Month,” which has historically been the month of May. Groups of riders from all over the state will unite and converge on the state capitol building in Montgomery to draw motorists' attention to the presence of motorcycles on our highways and to let Alabama's lawmakers know the motorcyclists in Alabama now have a strong voice. Don’t miss out on what looks to be the most historic gathering of motorcycles ever in Alabama.

post_content: Our Italian Day was originally scheduled for June 30, the day after the Big Storm. Many people had no power, the streets were littered with debris, and many roads were not passable. We are going to try it again, it will be a little cooler and hopefully PEPCO will have restored power by October. We will have Italian motorcycles (Ducati) and Italian cars (Ferrari), a car and bike show with fabulous trophies, free Italian food, a spaghetti eating contest, opera music playing, and much more!

post_content: Want to see eagles, red tail hawks, burrowing owls, and turkey vultures up close? Join us Sunday, February 17, 2013 for our 8th annual “Bikers Soar For Wildlife” motorcycle ride sponsored by the Adobe Mountain Wildlife Center Auxiliary (AMWCA). All proceeds go to help rescue, rehabilitate and care for the hundreds of animals that come to the Adobe Mountain Wildlife Center each year.The ride starts and ends at Buffalo Chip Saloon in Cave Creek. Sign-up is 8–9:30 am. Breakfast will be available for purchase on a first come basis. As always participants will enjoy a great lunch, music, a raffle, auction and a large display of animals courtesy of the volunteers at Adobe Mountain Wildlife Center.Pre-registration is $25/rider, $30/couple. The first 200 who pre-register will receive a ride shirt and pin. After February 8, 2013, registration prices are $30/single and $40/couple.The AMWCA is a 501c3 organization. All donations are tax deductible. For more information you can call the Center at 623.587.0139, e-mail Sharon at bikerssoarforwildlife@hotmail.com or visit the website at www.azwildlifecenter.net or Facebook at www.facebook.com/azwildlifecenter.

post_content: Forget the sleigh — Santa will be leading our second annual Holiday Light Parade on two wheels! Bring the whole family to watch this one-of-a-kind holiday spectacle. Or, better yet, join in the festivities. All makes and models welcome. Plus, the best decorated bike will be awarded this year's "Blazin' Yule" trophy. Pre-register your bike by November 19 and you'll receive free H-D Museum admission and a gift. Your $10 entry fee will be donated to Arts@Large.
print_desc:
Harley-Davidson motorcycles bring heart-thumping adventure, life-changing freedom and a bit of rebellion into the lives of people around the world. But whether you were born to be wild – or mild – makes no difference at the Harley-Davidson Museum in Milwaukee, Wisconsin.

Much more than a nostalgia trip for motorcycle enthusiasts, the Museum offers a glimpse of American history and culture like you’ve never seen before – through the successes and trials of an iconic American company. Interactive, eye-catching exhibits present an unparalleled collection of legendary stories of our nation’s last century. Located on 20 acres in downtown Milwaukee, the Museum offers a restaurant, café, retail store and park-like outdoor spaces.
reg_desc: Visit h-dmuseum.com to download the registration form.

post_title: 41st Annual Baldwin (Michigan) Blessing of Bikes Festival
post_content: May 17-19, 2013.“Paragon Rocks the Blessing” at 41st annual Blessing of Bikes festival will be held in Baldwin, Michigan.Festival starts on Friday, May 17 and ends on Sunday, May 19.There will be vendors set up all over the town of Baldwin coming from all over the country, and giant food fest all weekend. Camping is available. (No vendor set up at the airport.) Blessing will be on Sunday, May 19 at the airport sponsored by Para Dice Motorcycle Club. Gates will open at 9 am and donation is $5 per bike.More than 40,000 bikers come every year from all over the country.Location: Baldwin, Michigan
print_desc: There will be vendors set up all over the town of Baldwin coming from all over the country, and giant food fest all weekend. Camping is available. (No vendor set up at the airport.) Blessing will be on Sunday, May 19 at the airport sponsored by Para Dice Motorcycle Club. Gates will open at 9 am.More than 40,000 bikers come every year from all over the country.

print_desc: Come see new and used motorcycles, vendors, parts and accessories. Enter your bike in the Best of the Best custom Bike show for cash prizes. Be entertained by bands, special guests, bike builders, and stars from Sons of Anarchy. There is something for the whole family to see.

post_content: Come see new and used motorcycles, vendors, parts and accessories.Enter your bike in the Best of the Best custom Bike show for cash prizes.Be entertained by bands, special guests, bike builders, and much more.  There is something for the whole family to see.    Admission is $15 for adults, $7 for children 6–12 years old, children 5 and under are free.Expo show hours on Saturday are 10 am–5 pm and Sunday 10 am–5 pm.For more information call 978.688.8888 or visit our website at www.kevmarv.com.

post_title: Harley-Davidson of New York City Celebrates Harley's Heroes
post_content: In honor of Veterans Day, H-D of NYC is rolling out the red carpet for our New York Area veterans!Disabled American Veterans National Service Officers, all disabled veterans themselves, will provide free benefits counseling to all veterans. Additionally, representatives from other veteran service organizations such as The American Legion, Veterans of Foreign Wars, and the Purple Heart, as well as military riding clubs, will also be in attendance to similarly counsel veterans, free of charge, and provide them with options and information.And, because DAV is doing their part to help our veterans, we're doing our part to help them. We'll be selling special edition H-D of NYC Veterans merchandise, with 100 percent of those proceeds going to the DAV.Join us and help salute Harley's Heroes!
print_desc: In honor of Veterans Day, H-D of NYC is rolling out the red carpet for our New York Area veterans. Disabled American Veterans National Service Officers, all disabled veterans themselves, will provide free benefits counseling to all veterans. Additionally, representatives from other veteran service organizations such as The American Legion, Veterans of Foreign Wars, and the Purple Heart, as well as military riding clubs, will also be in attendance to similarly counsel veterans, free of charge, and provide them with options and information. And because DAV is doing their part to help our veterans, we're doing our part to help them. We'll be selling special edition H-D of NYC Veterans merchandise, with 100 percent of those proceeds going to the DAV. Join us and help salute Harley's Heroes.
reg_desc: No need to register. Just come on in.

We are currently searching for vendors to display products indoors.

post_content: White Rose Thunder is a premier motorcycle event.  It will feature flat track motorcycle racing, concerts, live entertainment, bike shows, custom builders, field events, biker games, vendors, vintage cycles, swap meets, and more. There will be motorcycle rides throughout south central Pennsylvania and northern Maryland, during one of our most beautiful times of the year.  Additionally, there are numerous other historical, geographic, cultural  and other attractions to fulfill all interests. WRT will be a full throttle experience for all riders and motorcycle enthusiasts.

post_title: Thunder in the Valley Motorcycle Rally
post_content: Johnstown's annual Thunder in the Valley motorcycle rally is held the fourth weekend in June. While the City of Johnstown serves as the hub of the rally, related events take place throughout the entire Johnstown region. The natural beauty of the Johnstown region is an attraction in and of itself, where its winding back roads lure bikers seeking great rides. Feature entertainment is scattered around the venues and offer something for everyone. Several major motorcycle manufacturers offer a display for new models and demo rides. Come join us for one of American’s top motorcycle rallies!

Come join us for one of American’s top motorcycle rallies.

post_title: 3rd Annual Salems Bikers Gone Wild To Gift Childrens SMILES
post_content: A local non-profit community-effort toy run, 50/50 raffle to buy new toys for the family visitation rooms at the State of Oregon Child Welfare Office, after run party at the Hitchin’ Post, 8046 River Road NE. Everyone welcome.
print_desc: A local non-profit community-effort toy run, 50/50 raffle to buy new toys for the family visitation rooms at the State of Oregon Child Welfare Office, after run party at the Hitchin’ Post, 8046 River Road NE. Everyone welcome.
benefits: 12 Oxford Houses, Soar program (men out of prison), SOS club, The ROCC, State of Oregon Foster Children Office Visiting Room, New Options, Moms Mentors, All clean and sober enviroments and recovery.
reg_desc: Bikes not required, ride, drive, bike, skateboard, etc. We will find a place for you.

post_content: Motorcyclepedia motorcycle museum in Newburgh, New York, will be starting a speaker series on Wednesday, January 23, 2013. Each month a new topic will be presented. Starting off the series is a presentation, How to Avoid a Ticket: What the cops look for on your motorcycle. This will be a two hour presentation by retired Police Chief Peter Miller. He has 34 years police experience, is a former Motor Officer and MSF Rider Coach. This is a thorough presentation on New York’s vehicle and traffic laws specific to motorcycles, motorcycle safety, a brief discussion on the controversial motorcycle safety checkpoints and other related topics. Please feel free to contact me with any questions at info@motorcyclepediamuseums.com or you can call me directly at 845.224.5439. You can view our website at www.motorcyclepediamuseums.org.

post_content: Step off your bike and onto the grounds at Carlisle. With free onsite bike parking, Carlisle Bike Fest offers an experience like no other. Bike Fest is crafted with the rider in mind and is the Mid-Atlantic’s premier motorcycle event. Tens of thousands of bikes, trikes and open-air fanatics cruise in for everything from non-stop entertainment to breathtaking local rides, industry guests, custom builders, stunt shows, test rides, special prizes which often include motorcycle giveaways and live bands all weekend. Plus, if you haven’t experienced a Rat Rod Revival, come check out this bare-bones restoration movement celebrating builders’ creativity and resourcefulness. You don’t want to miss this three-day celebration of all things motorcycle.

post_title: 10th Annual WVMC Vintage MC Swap Meet and Show
post_content: One-day event open to the public at 8 a.m. Pedestrian admission is $2; parking $5 per carload. The meet will be held concurrent with the swap meet sponsored by the North Cascade Street Rod Association, featuring vintage motorcycles, cars, trucks, parts, and accessories. The two events fill the fairground complex. Check the club website at http://www.washingtonvintagemotorcyclists.org/Events.html for more information. This year the event will include a show of vintage motorcycles, featuring American classics and other marques. Indoor stall rental fee: 10’x10’ at $30 each, or bike sale stall at $15 per bike. Open to vendors at 6 am. Stall reservations and fees must be received prior to April 5, 2013. Contact WVM, c/o Mark Cattarin at 360.223.3190 for information. E-mail: marcuscc@comcast.net. Another great vintage bike meet, the 28th annual Classic & Vintage MC Swap Meet Show ‘N Shine, is on Sunday, April 28 in Tsawwassen, BC, Canada, at the South Delta Recreation Centre, just 60 miles north of Mt. Vernon. Call Todd Copan at 604.299.0020. Be sure to bring your passport!
print_desc: One-day event open to the public at 8 a.m. The meet will be held concurrent with the swap meet sponsored by the North Cascade Street Rod Association, featuring vintage motorcycles, cars, trucks, parts, and accessories. The two events fill the fairground complex. Check the club website at for more information. This year the event will include a show of vintage motorcycles, featuring American classics and other marques.
reg_desc: Pedestrian admission is $2; parking $5/carload. Indoor stall rental fee: 10’x10’ at $30 each, or bike sale stall at $15 per bike. Open to vendors at 6 am. Stall reservations and fees must be received prior to April 5, 2013.

post_content: The American Legion Riders are members of the American Legion who are also motorcycle enthusiasts. They can be found participating in parades, partaking in motorcycling events, and supporting the communities in which they live, work, and play. Members of the ALR come from the Legion, the Legion Auxilliary, and the Sons of the American Legion. The American Legion Riders were formed......to participate in parades and other ceremonies that are in keeping with the Aims and Purposes of the American Legion.      ...to promote motorcycle safety programs and to provide a social atmosphere for American Legion members who share the same interest.      ...to use our Association to promote and support programs of the American Legion. The American Legion Riders is not a M/C, and does not practice M/C rules or regulations. The American Legion Riders is family-oriented, just as is its parent organization: the American Legion.

Members of the ALR come from the Legion, the Legion Auxilliary, and the Sons of the American Legion. The American Legion Riders were formed......to participate in parades and other ceremonies that are in keeping with the Aims and Purposes of the American Legion.      ...to promote motorcycle safety programs and to provide a social atmosphere for American Legion members who share the same interest.      ...to use our Association to promote and support programs of the American Legion. The American Legion Riders is not a M/C, and does not practice M/C rules or regulations. The American Legion Riders is family-oriented, just as is its parent organization: the American Legion.

We support programs to educate drivers, legislators and motorcyclists aimed toward education and safety.

post_content: Official Start time of the rally is Friday at 12 noon early entry Wednesday and Thursday is an additional $10 per night.No one under 21 admitted. No ATVs allowed, BYOB. Convenience stores nearby, no glass bottles, onsite camping, RVs welcome, no hookups, hot showers, contests, Miss Thunder Rally Contest, shaving crème rasslin’, poker run, bike games, burn-out pit, live music, vendors, bike show and much more! Event is rain or shine. The event is BYOB. Convenience stores located on Hwy 441 Bypass. Ice sold on the premises at entrance gate. No electrical or water hookups available in the camping area. Hot showers are located in camping area and near exit gate. Port-a-johns are located throughout the grounds. Generators are welcome. This is a motorcycle rally. There may be noise and music all night long. Remember, your picture may be taken by fellow rally goers. If you don’t want anyone to see it later, don’t show it at the rally. Not responsible for accidents, theft or loss of property. Please be safe and considerate of others. Ride safe and have fun.

post_content: This will be a road trip to the 56th annual Whiskey Flat Days 2013 event in Kernville. Meet at 11 am at San Jose Harley-Davidson on Friday for group ride to Bakersfield (Depart at 11:30 am). Hotel stay overnight in Bakersfield on Friday and Saturday. Meet at 9 am on Saturday at Zingo’s Café located at 201 Buck Owens Boulevard, Bakersfield for group ride to the event. Saturday night will feature a group dinner and return home on Sunday morning.

Meet at 9 am on Saturday at Zingo’s Café located at 201 Buck Owens Boulevard, Bakersfield for group ride to the event. Saturday night will feature a group dinner and return home on Sunday morning.
reg_desc: To register for this event, or for more ride details, visit our ride webpage.

post_content: Our annual spring open house kicks off our riding season right. Stop in and see our newly remodeled pre-owned showroom and take advantage of store-wide savings on H-D Genuine licensed products. Enter for your chance to win up to $1,000 in Heritage gift cards when you spend $100 at the store. We're choosing 30 winners so come on out! Also, we will be providing free hot dogs and popcorn for everyone! Let's start the year out together!
organizer_desc: Our annual Spring Open House kicks off our riding season in style. Great local motorcycle related vendors, food, drinks, music, and more! Come celebrate another year with us! post_content: Here’s your chance to turn those old boxes in the garage into cash! Join us for a day of fun! Bring out all your Harley-Davidson stuff to sell or come out and see what other people are selling. Seller details: All sellers are responsible for setting up their own space. You are allowed a space approximately 8ft by 8ft. Please ask if you need more. You must bring your own tables, tents, extension chords, etc. All vendors must be here prior to the event to setup. No one is permitted to leave their vehicles at their spaces during the event. All vehicles will have a designated area in the lot to park in order to alleviate any further event congestion. This is a Harley-Davidson Rummage, please do not bring items not related to Harley-Davidson. Thank you and good luck! Space is limited and fills up quickly. Please RSVP via e-mail at sgulo@heritagehd.com or call 630.388.1684.

post_content: The Modified Motorcycle Association of California invites everyone interested in preserving your rights, to join us at the annual Freedom Rally at the State Capitol. Group photo at 10:30 am. Meet and hear legislators and invited speakers. If you would like to help defray the rally expenses paid by MMA of California; then please send your donations (checks payable to MMA of California) to the office. To sponsor a parking meter(s) it costs $25 per meter on L Street. Further information please call Heather at 916.470.2938 or Bobbie 916.912.0459 anyone, club or business that donates gets a sleeve that goes over the meter with your name on it. Each parking space allows four motorcycles.

post_content: Interested in learning to ride or want to brush up on your basic riding skills? post_content: We are excited about our upcoming 13th Annual “Ride For Life” event and want to share with you why we would like you to participate this year. First question to ask yourself is, "Are you or anyone you know affected by cancer?" I’m sure that the majority of you answered yes. You probably know then how hard it can be on the families and what a financial burden this can be. “Ride For Life” was started by a friend and fellow rider, Mr. Dan Ertz, as a way to raise funds for the Inland Northwest “Cancer Patient Care” organization.  “Cancer Patient Care” is a non-profit organization that provides assistance to families in need that are dealing with cancer. They help with things such as utility bill assistance, or gasoline for your car to get to a chemotherapy treatment or as simple as just putting food on the table. Sometimes the person affected may be the bread winner in the family and can’t work or because their child or spouse may be the patient and they have been forced to take time off from their jobs. Medical Insurance does not cover things like this and now they just don’t have the means to pay for these things. These are our friends, our neighbors and in some cases our own families. Let's all join together to help them. Remember, all of the money raised by this event stays local in the Inland Northwest.The bottom line is Cancer Patient Care is a great non-prophet organization helping local families suffering with cancer. They can not do it without the generous contributions of folk like you.Please join us and "RIDE FOR LIFE."
print_desc: This is great fun filled event starting with a fabulous ride around Lake Couer D Alene, music, food, raffles and 2 different auctions. Please join us and "Ride for Life."
reg_desc: See our booth at the Inland Northwest MC Show or Lawrence's MC in CDA or Lone Wolf Harley-Davidson in Spokane or go to our website www.rideforlifeidaho.net.

post_title: Untold Stories: Built for Speed, The History & Evolution of Harley-Davidson Racing
post_content: Race fuel. Burning rubber. Checkered Flags. The Wrecking Crew. Springfield. Indy. Daytona. From Walter Davidson’s two-day endurance victory in 1908 to Eddie Krawiec’s dominating 2012 National Hot Rod Association (NHRA) Pro Stock Motorcycle Championship, Harley-Davidson has a rich and unrivaled racing history. Come bask in the glory, and experience Built for Speed: The History & Evolution of Harley-Davidson Racing. Hosted by AMA Pro XR1200 racer and Harley-Davidson Consumer Events Director Paul James, you’ll meet and hear from: • Three-time and defending NHRA Pro Stock Motorcycle Champions and current class top speed record holder Eddie Krawiec of the Screamin’ Eagle/Vance & Hines drag racing team • Three-time NHRA Pro Stock Motorcycle Champion and current class ET record holder Andrew Hines of the Screamin’ Eagle/Vance & Hines drag racing team • Three-time AMA Pro Racing Grand National Champion Harley-Davidson/Screamin’ Eagle factory flat track racer Kenny Coolbeth • Nine-time AMA Pro Grand National Champion, all-time record AMA Pro Grand National race winner, 3-time AMA Pro Athlete of the Year and AMA Hall of Fame member Scott Parker • Harley-Davidson Museum Archives Manager Bill Jackson Buy Tickets Online at www.h-dmuseum.comor just call 877.HD.MUSEUM (414.287.2789).
print_desc: From Walter Davidson’s two-day endurance victory in 1908 to Eddie Krawiec’s dominating 2012 National Hot Rod Association (NHRA) Pro Stock Motorcycle Championship, Harley-Davidson has a rich and unrivaled racing history. Come bask in the glory, and experience Built for Speed: The History & Evolution of Harley-Davidson Racing.
reg_desc: Buy tickets online at www.h-dmuseum.com or call 877.HD.MUSEUM (414.287.2789).

post_content: As Easter fades into the rear view, motorcyclists are looking forward to the 4th Annual Blessing of the Bikes at Harley-Davidson of Asheville.  Many will notice the change in venue from MR Motorcycle in previous years.  The Blessing will provide an opportunity for all motorcyclists to be blessed for a safe riding season and an opportunity for fellowship while promoting bike safety, along with a positive image of motorcycling to the community.  100% of all donations will benefit the Asheville Buncombe Community Christian Ministry (ABCCM).   This nondenominational ceremony is open to all riders, all ages and all makes and models of motorcycles, including dirt, street and custom bikes.There will be several ministers on site from various organizations such as the Asheville Buncombe Community Christian Ministry, the Christian Motorcyclists Association (CMA) and the Freedom Biker Church.A catered lunch will be provided for a minimum donation of $10 in either cash or hygiene items (tooth brushes, tooth paste, dental floss, shaving cream, disposable razors, aftershave, deodorant, cologne, Tums/Rolaids, alcohol-free mouthwash, shampoo, bar soap, laundry soap, etc.).The event is scheduled from 2pm-4pm, rain or shine, with live music by Turnbridge, a live simulcast by 95.7 FM The Choice, food by Okie Dokies Smokehouse, prizes and a 50/50 drawing.  After the event, attendees are invited to an ice cream to meet the residents at the Veterans’ Restoration Quarters (VRQ) at 1329 Tunnel Road.Learn more online at HDofAsheville.com.

Live music by Turnbridge, a live simulcast by 95.7 FM The Choice, food by Okie Dokies Smokehouse, prizes and a 50/50 drawing.  After the event, attendees are invited to an ice cream to meet the residents at the Veterans’ Restoration Quarters (VRQ) at 1329 Tunnel Road.

post_title: Sonny Barger Presents: Dead In 5 Heartbeats -The Movie
post_content: Sonny Barger presents Dead In 5 Heartbeats the movie. Showing at Silver Cinemas/Super Saver 8 on April 5–7 at 1 pm, 3:15 pm, 5:30 pm, 7:45 pm, and 10 pm. Sonny Barger, Jeff Santo, and Jeff Black will be at the 7:45 pm showing on April 6.Produced by American Legend Sonny Barger. Directed by Independent Filmmaker, Jeff Santo. Shot on location in Arizona, May and June of 2012, featuring real Motorcycle Clubs and their Clubhouses. Dead In 5 Heartbeats is an authentic look into the MC World, its narrative pours from the hearts of two California Infidelz Motorcycle Club Members. One is the former President, Patch Kinkade, who transferred to Arizona to find solitude after a family tragedy. On the flip side, Angelo Timmons, a single father and Seargeant at Arms with over 20 years of dedication to the California Infidelz decides to turn against his brothers to give his son a better life. When a newly patched-in Club Member is mysteriously gunned down, Patch Kinkade is called back into town to help his former Club. Dead In 5 Heartbeats is a story of two friends with opposing positions, who together discover the true meaning of their Motorcycle Club Brotherhood.

post_title: Beartooth Rally and Iron Horse Rodeo
post_content: The Beartooth Rally and Iron Horse Rodeo take place each year in the sweet little mountain town of Red Lodge Montana. Located in the heart of the northern Rockies, just over the hill from Yellowstone National Park and virtually at the base of the incredible Beartooth Pass the riding is out of this world. With great poker runs both Friday and Saturday, the outrageous comedy of Bag Lady Sue, Fusion Fight League MMA Cage fights, street parties in the evenings and on Sunday afternoon the Iron Horse Rodeo there is something for everybody. Red Lodge has great food lodging and some of the friendliest people anywhere. Camping is available. For more information go to beartoothrally.com or call Tim at 406.446.2022. This is Montana’s Rally come out let's go for a ride.

post_title: Do Wa Diddy 30th Annual Pig Roast
post_content: The Tenino Motorcycle Drill Team is having our 30th annual Scholarship Pig Roast Fund Raiser. We have been at this for 30 years raising money for the community and persons in need. We operate as a 501 C 7 IRS recognized charity. Our main focus (other than starting off many parades and local community events) is the Tenino Washington High School graduating students that are in need of some extra financial support. The Tenino Motorcycle Drill Team’s $1,000 scholarship has helped as many as 11 young adults in a single year. The number of scholarships is based on the number of attendees so please come support our community.

post_content: The National Demo Tour will be bringing more than 14 new 2013 Victory motorcycles to Southern California Victory for riders and motorcycle enthusiasts to demo ride on March 8–9, in Brea, California, from 9:30 am to 6 pm. See one of the 18-wheelers from Victory’s national demo fleet provide more Victory products to view, product specialists to answer questions and more time and flexibility to look around, while getting a first-hand experience at testing out the product. It’s a great opportunity for riders and motorcycle enthusiasts to try one or more of the many different Victory models. Riders can enjoy as many bikes as they want, but must have a valid motorcycle license and adhere to riding gear requirements and safety. Southern California Victory will also explain to riders how a particular bike can be fitted to them by adjusting the handlebars, seat height, and suspension. Attendees will be signed up on a first-come, first-serve basis at the dealership each day.Saturday only there will also be a vendor market with free food, drinks, music and tents displaying products for sale, information on local charitable organizations and more for families to come and enjoy. For more information about the dealership, visit Southern California Victory online at www.socalvictory.com.

post_title: Cruisin' for St. Jude Children's Hospital
post_content: Heritage Harley-Davidson is hosting this annual fundraising ride/event to raise money that will help St. Jude Children's Research Hospital find new treatments for childhood cancer and other catastrophic diseases. You can help St. Jude continue its lifesaving work against pediatric diseases with your attendance/donations. The after party will take place directly after the ride. Heritage will provide free food, beverages, bands, and so much more! We'll have great vendors coming out and plenty of free flowing beer (please drink responsibly!) Also there will be plenty of opportunities for you to score big with our raffles and silent auction! All proceeds go to the St. Jude Children's Hospital.To pre-register and/or donate to the event, visit:   https://waystohelp.stjude.org/sjVPortal/public/event/page/displayEventPage.do?eventId=346772&programId=51  (you will have to create a username and password to do this)We will also have pre-registration the day of the event starting at 9 am–11 am. Entrance fee for the ride and after party is $25/person. The ride will begin at 11 am and we will ride until 1 pm with a safety stop in the middle. Again, all proceeds go to the St. Jude Children's Hospital.For any additional questions, comments, or ways you can volunteer to help make this event successful, please contact Steve Gulo at 630.388.1684 or via e-mail at sgulo@heritagehd.com.Thank you so much for your participation!

post_content: Click here for the best Florida Travel SpotsClick here for the Daytona Bike Week Vendor LocationsThe inaugural running of the Daytona 200 took place on January 24, 1937, and marked the first year of Daytona Bike Week. The race took place on a beach and road course south of Daytona Beach. It was discontinued in 1942 because of World War II, although riders still showed up for an unofficial party. By 1961 the race was moved to Daytona International Speedway where it still runs today.Today Daytona Bike Week spans 10 days in March, with the city of Daytona Beach and its environs hosting up to 500,000 riders every year. The rally now includes bike shows, demo rides, guided tours, vendors, concerts,party spots and, of course, races. Bike Week can be overwhelming for the first timer, so we’ve put together some information that will help you navigate the rally.Click on the links below for more information about Daytona Bike Week at Thunderpress.net:      Ride Guide    Beach Cruising    Law & Party Guide
print_desc:
The inaugural running of the Daytona 200 took place on January 24, 1937, and marked the first year of Daytona Bike Week. The race took place on a beach and road course south of Daytona Beach. It was discontinued in 1942 because of World War II, although riders still showed up for an unofficial party. By 1961 the race was moved to Daytona International Speedway where it still runs today.

 

 

Today Daytona Bike Week spans 10 days in March, with the city of Daytona Beach and its environs hosting up to 500,000 riders every year. The rally now includes bike shows, demo rides, guided tours, vendors, concerts,party spots and, of course, races. Bike Week can be overwhelming for the first timer, so we’ve put together some information that will help you navigate the rally.

post_content: BRINGING YOU THE BEST AND THE BIGGEST 5-STATE EVENT ON THE EAST COAST.Motorcycle enthusiasts are descending on the Okemo Valley for the Iron Adventure Run. From the moment you arrive, you'll be amazed by the beauty of our region of the USA and the bikes and riders that come to visit.Activities include a bike show, bike games, parade of bikes, scavenger hunt, and vendors. Riders will cover at least 110 miles on Route 100. Why 110 miles? Because 2013 marks Harley-Davidson’s 110th anniversary of making motorcycles. Harley Owners Group, the official riding club of Harley-Davidson, also celebrates its 30th anniversary this year.Other guided destination rides include President Calvin Coolidge’s Historic Site, Crowley Cheese Factory, Vermont Country Stores, maple sugar houses, and covered bridges, as well as many other scenic attractions found along Routes 131, Route 103, and Route 11. All are sure to make some riding memories for our honored guests here in the Okemo Valley region. Riders may also venture off on their own for the opportunity to stop wherever they like to shop, dine, relax, and enjoy all the region has to offer.Come ride with us!http://www.ironadventure.com

post_content: Rows of stunning and memorable vintage bikes from around the world, gleaming in the sun. Tables piled with interesting parts and fragments of motorcycle history in a swap meet. Classic and stylish scooters in the new Scooters! exhibit. Dirt track racers and some of the men and women who raced them in Dirt Track Heroes, the newest Museum exhibit. A Sunday ride on some of Iowa’s best back roads. If this array of motorcycling experiences brings a smile to your face, plan to attend the Vintage Rally June 8 & 9 at the National Motorcycle Museum in Anamosa, Iowa.While the Museum in its new location holds over 400 fabulous motorcycles and thousands of great pieces of art and memorabilia, the bike show at the third annual Vintage Rally weekend will be when even more fine machines line up out front for review. Judging will result in nearly 40 awards for owners of the best machines, including the best original unrestored bikes for the Preservation Award. Enter your vintage bike, street, competition, custom, even mini, 1987 or earlier, scooter or dirt track bike, in the bike show. Bike show awards are sponsored by Motorcycle Classics magazine. Got a nice vintage cafe racer? The Ace Café will sponsor a special Cafe Racer award during the Bike Show.Be part of the dedication of the new Dirt Track Heroes exhibition and take in over 20 great dirt track racers, steel shoes, helmets, leathers, photos, posters and vintage action film footage. You’ll also be able to check out other additions to the National Motorcycle Museum’s exhibits which are always changing and expanding.Walk the swap meet and pick up parts for your projects or add to your memorabilia collection. Or reserve your own swap meet space if you need to trim your collection.We have invited dirt track racers and other Hall of Fame inductees, enthusiastic to sign autographs and tell you their important stories. Or listen to interesting characters from racing’s past, racers, tuners and collectors during the entertaining and educational panel discussions. And you can sign up for the Sunday morning ride and lunch hosted by Motorcycle Classics magazine.Mark your calendar and plan to attend June 8 & 9! Admission for this event will be $10 a day, $20 for the weekend or $30 for the weekend with lunch on Sunday. The event price includes admission to the Museum. Children 12 and under are free when accompanied by an adult.Watch the National Motorcycle Museum website, www.nationalmcmuseum.org for further event details, the activities schedule and lodging information as they are finalized. If you can’t find information you need on the website, call the Museum at 319.462.3925.

post_content: What better time to join us for a great ride than the 90th Anniversary of the Rally?!  Progressive Insurance Laconia Motorcycle Week is stronger than ever as we roll into our 90thcelebration from June 8th-16th, 2013.  As America’s Original Riding Rally, you can expect the ultimate riding experience around the Lakes Region and all of New Hampshire as our residents and businesses alike welcome you - our visitors from all around the world for this momentous occasion. post_content: Motorcycle  Extravaganza!!!March 23rd & 24th 2013Allentown Fairgrounds, Allentown, PA                                   Sat 10-6 and Sun 10-5Admission is only $10.00 Children under 12 FREE                                      Groups of 20 or more contact us for Designated Parking and Discounted Admission  (also no waiting in line)SPECIAL GUESTS                                       JUST ANNOUNCED!!!!Joining us Sat & Sun –Signing Autographs and taking photos.Cody Connelly                              Previously from Discovery's American Choppers.&WXW -World Extreme WrestlingC4NationThe grapplers and gladiators, the finest and fiercest competitors this sport has to offer.Come and check it out!  Even if it’s chilly, raining or snowing, no worries our event is  “INDOORS" and heated if needed with over 250 Vendors and a USED PARTS & THINGS SWAP MEET.  Cars are also invited and welcome to "Gather in the Lot".  Hot-Rods, Antiques, Custom or Classic...come show off what you got!!! You don't have to own, ride or know about motorcycles to enjoy this event.  We offer a low admission fee and a family friendly atmosphere. Bring the kids!!. 12 and under are free. Walk around, have some lunch, have a beer, or just sit back and enjoy the show!!!  Have your photo taken at the Photo Booth on a Custom Built Bike with our Extravaganza Girls. Live Entertainment both days by The Crabby Bums's and Door Prizes every two hours.Enter the Open Bike Show and Tattoo Contests for 1st Place Cash Prizes and a Custom One of a Kind Trophy made by Sims Designs. Tattoo Contest (Sponsored by Comfort Suites, Allentown) is only $10. Entry fee per category (Best Color, Best Black & White, Most Unusual & Most Realistic)                                                                                    Bike Show Entry Fee is only $30. And Includes a 2 day VIP Show Pass. Classes are (Antique, Sport, Custom & Radical) Don’t just watch it, be in it and win it!!!How about a new Tattoo? Get some ink by Famous & local featured artists. Ride, trailer or drag your bike to the Bike Blessing on Sunday. (Weather permitting)Agri-Plex Center is over 60,000 SQ FT and located at the Allentown Fairgrounds, 1825 W. Chew Street, Allentown, PA Easily accessible from major highways and only two hours from New York City and areas of New Jersey. The famous Lehigh Valley Farmers Market is right next door...and PARKING IS AWAYS FREE!! This event is growing to be the largest motorcycle event in Pennsylvania. We hope you agree and will join us.... A % of all proceeds are donated to P.A.N.D.A.S Research and UMSFL  The Comfort Suites- 3712 Hamilton Boulevard,  Allentown, PA is offering special room rates of only $60.00 (plus tax) for Motorcycle Extravaganza Guests to make it an affordable stay for everyone. Call now to book your stay (610) 437-9100   AFTER PARTY - Linxs Bar & GrillSaturday Night- 7:30pm till??                                                               Comfort Suites-3712 Hamilton Blvd, Allentown VENDOR INFO- ALL vendors are accepted on a first come basis and spaces fill up fast. Vendors selling only used parts & things can have unlimited space in the Swap Meet Area (outside - Big top if bad weather) for only a $25.00 Registration fee.  If you are interested in being a Vendor contact us for a Vendor Registration Form. Interested in being a Sponsor? We have investment opportunities to fit your marking budget.  For more information call 732 295 2953 or email us at events@mextrava.comVisit our website at www.mextrava.com

post_content: SuperTrapp Industries, Inc. and Quaker Steak & Lube  partnered up once again to host their fifth annual SuperTrapp Industries Bike Nite Food Drives. Attendees will have an opportunity for a chance to win $1,000 worth of motorcycle accessories from SuperTrapp the night of the event. It doesn’t stop there though. SuperTrapp wants everyone to come together for a great cause.SuperTrapp Industries is asking everyone to bring a minimum $5 cash donation with them. SuperTrapp will match each donation dollar for dollar up to $2,000. Those that make a donation at the SuperTrapp Industries display trailer located in the parking lot will receive a free, commemorative, “Fuel Your Passion While You Feed The Hungry” SuperTrapp Bike Nite Food Drive T-shirt.  For every $5 an individual donates, SuperTrapp Industries will allow them to enter their name for a chance to win the SuperTrapp prize pack. Winner must be present to win.The more attendees donate, the better their chances of winning.          All donations will benefit various, local area food banks. Mark your calendars!  SuperTrapp Industries Bike Nite Food Drives will take place this summer at the following two locations: Where:  Quaker Steak & Lube – Sheffield, OHWhen:   Thursday – June 20, 2013 from 5pm – 10pmWho:     To benefit the Second Harvest of North Central Ohio   SuperTrapp Industries will reach out to local riders and enthusiasts by displaying their several brands of performance products including SuperTrapp, Kerker, Road Legends, Jardine, JayBrake and FPS Racing at their 48 foot display trailer. SuperTrapp Industries staff will be on hand to answer questions, pass out catalogs and collect food bank donations. For more info, visit www.SuperTrapp.com or call 216-265-8400.  Request complimentary catalogs and e-newsletters of SuperTrapp Industries’ various brands by clicking on the “Contact Us” tab.   Become a fan of the SuperTrapp Industries family of brands such as SuperTrapp, Jardine and JayBrake on Facebook. Follow SuperTrapp and Jardine on Twitter.  SuperTrapp, Kerker, Jardine, JayBrake and FPS Racing products are made in the U.S.A.   For 42 years, SuperTrapp Industries, Inc. has been a leading manufacturer of performance exhaust products for motorcycle, ATV and automotive applications. In addition to their signature tunable disc diffuser exhaust systems, SuperTrapp manufactures the Kerker brand of exhaust systems, Road Legends Series, designed by master bike builder, Paul Yaffe and TC Racing exhausts, designed by master ATV engine builder, Tom Carlson.  SuperTrapp also manufactures the JayBrake (www.jbrake.com) product line which includes forward foot controls, handlebar controls, foot pegs, grips, brake calipers, and other motorcycle accessories to fit Harley-Davidson and American V-Twin motorcycles.SuperTrapp Industries is also the proud owner and manufacturer of Jardine Performance Products (www.jardineproducts.com) which include exhausts, backrests, highway bars, forward controls, and fender kits as well as FPS Racing (www.FPSRacing.com) which include high performance radiators, oil coolers and accessories directed towards the off road dirt bike, ATV & UTV markets.  Made in the U.S.A.

The more attendees donate, the better their chances of winning.

post_content: Ride & Rock with the crew from Independent Motorcycles and Mogollon. This ride is brought to you by the Beard Brothers of Independent Motorcycles and sponsored in part by Chuck Franklin Law. Stops include: Jolie’s Place, Dirty Dogg Saloon, and AJ's Baseline Grill.This ride is bound to be one of the best rides and parties of Arizona Bike Week Pre-Rally’s days. There will be live music, great people and a kickback ride, all for a great cause “Sounds of Autism.”So get your groove on support a local shop a local charity and play with us!Sounds of Autism is a 501c3 non-profit charity Mission is to integrate autistic children and their families back into the community, using love, support and modern technology. To begin the initiative we are using our VOICE to inspire people and provide knowledge about the challenges created by Autism Spectrum Disorder. It is the VOICES of our supporters that will help spread awareness and contribute to the education of autism.

post_content: Sunday, April 28th, 2013 8:30 am–4 pmStarting point is the Chatterbox Drive-In Restaurant on Route 15 in Augusta, NJ.Come out to join us for the 5th annual Joann Miller Memorial Run (JAMM). Our ride ends with an (optional) cash lunch at the all new Rockaway River Barn. Great food, very reasonable prices too!Commemorative pins available for first 50 registrants! Rain date Sunday, May 5, 2013.Full details can be found here: www.wix.com/jammiv/runLast year we had more than 250 attendees! We hope to top that this year and you can make it happen!Hope to see you there.

post_title: LA Calendar Motorcycle Show Concours d' Elegance
post_content: The 2013 LA Calendar Motorcycle Show continues its now 22-year tradition as the premier outdoor streetbike show in America with a return to the Queen Mary's Seawalk Village, Long Beach, CA on Sunday July 14th.  Featured as always are the world's top Celebrity Builders displaying their newest bikes and competing in the Calendar Bike Building Championship & Concours d' Elegance, together with selected Industry Manufacturers and Vendors, and Calendar Girl Music Concert live performances. The Show always marks the world premier of the now 2014 FastDates.com Motorcycle PinUp Calendars featuring the world's top roadrace and custom motorcycles with the beautiful Calendar Kittens featured in the Calendars in attendance at the Show. For complete information go to: http://www.FastDates.com/BIKESHOW.HTMThe Calendar Show has broadened its focus from just the American V-Twin custom market, to embrace the growing Collector and Cafe Bike segments. The Show still includes its popular Pro Builder and Street Custom classes, Cafe Bike / Bobber, and Sportbike / Racebike Classes, and now the growing Collector Bike Market for European and Japanese Classics. Show Entries will be placed in a Concours d' Elegance displays on grass and patio walkways in the the Queen Mary's Seawalk Village. There is also an opportunity for Builders and Sellers to join the very affordable Seller's Showcase to market their bike or services, without having to purchase a full size Exhibitor Space.Among the top name custom bike builders expected to attend are former LA Calendar Show winners and featured FastDates.com Calendar bike builders Jim Giuffra and the Spokesmodels of AFT Metric Customs, Russell Mitchell / Exile Cycles, Shinya Kimura / Chabott Engineering, Richard Pollock / Mule Motorcycles, Todd Silicato / Todds Cycle, Chris Redpath / MotoGPwerks and many more.Headlining the live musical entertainment again this year is the all-girl Japanese Rock Band 'Nylon Pink' who will just be returning from their world music tour. Also featured will be some of Southern California's most talented and beautiful signer songwriters. While the Queen Mary's own gourmet restaurant culinary chefs will be preparing an incredible BBQ lunch menu that promises to exceed expectations of what is normally served at bike events. In all, it will be a full day of incredible bikes and builder, beautiful girls, music, food and beverages that will overwhelm all five of the human senses!The selected partners for the 2013 LA Calendar Motorcycle Show include Russ Brown Motorcycle Attorneys, Barnett's Bike Craft Magazine featuring retro and cafe bikes, Source Media's American V-Twin Group of magazines Hot Bike, Hot Bike Baggers and Street Chopper, and the motorcycle events monthly Thunder Press. The editors from each of the magazines will be in attendance to cover the event, assist in judging their sponsored classes, and choosing the top bikes to appear in their publications. Show producer Jim Gianatsis will be photographing the winning bikes to appear in the Magazines and the next FastDates.com Calendars. In addition to the coveted Best of Show and Class Awards, AFT Customs will present its Visionary Award Trophy for the most innovative and exciting bike at the event.The 2013 LA Calendar Motorcycle Show & Concours d' Elegance takes place on Sunday July 14th 10am-5pm at the The Queen Mary Seawalk Village,1126 Queens Highway, Long Beach, CA 90802. General Admission is just $20, or $40 VIP Admission which includes a BBQ Lunch w/ Beverage and Queen Mary ghost ship admission. Show capacity is limited and advance ticket purchase is suggested. post_title: Rock Store to Host Photo Shoot and Recipe Donation for Motorcyclists, Bikers & Community Members to Benefit WhatCanWe.org
post_content: Imagine this: Tons of motorcyclists, bikers and community members posing for professional photos with their favorite pooches and kitties at the world famous Rock Store!That’s exactly the scene that will take place on April 13, 2013  10 am–3 pm, as the Rock Store builds a special chapter in the WhatCanWe.org Kitchen Rescues: Recipes for People and Their Pets cookbook, the nonprofit’s annual fundraiser.  WhatCanWe.org raises funds to help licensed, nonprofit animal rescues offset the financial hardships faced due to overwhelming veterinary expenses.Simply bring your bike, your pet and your favorite recipe and a $100 donation to participate in the special chapter dedicated to the Rock Store and its patrons in Kitchen Rescues: Recipes for People and their Pets.Award-winning photographer Kathy Rappaport of Flash Frozen Photography will donate her professional photography talents to capture engaging photographs, which will be used in the cookbook.   With every $100 donation participants can include a recipe and a few words in the Rock Store chapter.Each recipe will include the photo taken April 13.All those donating will receive a professional keepsake portrait of their session.100% of all donations will go directly to helping licensed animal rescues. Bikers, motorcyclists and community members are invited to “drop in” for a photography session and donation at the Rock Store (30354 Mulholland Highway between Malibu Canyon/Las Virgenes Road and Kanan Road, Cornell, CA 91301).  To reserve a time, contact WhatCanWe.org or Flash Frozen Photography, 818.888.2280. About WhatCanWe.orgWhatCanWe.org™ started in 2012 to raise awareness and funds for licensed, nonprofit animal rescues in order to help offset the financial hardships most currently endure due to overwhelming veterinary expenses.  Today, every 1.5 seconds a homeless animal’s life is terminated in a shelter.  Fortunately, there is an army of benevolent rescue organizations that are on the front lines battling every day in an effort to positively change these numbers.  WhatCanWe.org is determined to change this situation by raising awareness and funds to offset these costs, and ultimately, to create nonprofit teaching veterinary clinics that offer low or no-cost veterinary care to licensed, nonprofit rescues.  To make a donation or for more information, visit www.whatcanwe.org and click on our Contact Page, or like us on Facebook, www.facebook.com/WhatCanWe?.org.  About The Rock Store The Rock Store is one of the most famous motorcyclist and biker hangouts in the world. Frequented by moto lovers as well as celebrities and nice people of all types, the Rock Store is an amazing place to get away from the city without going too far.  Located along famous Mulholland Highway halfway between Malibu and Calabasas, it's the perfect place to come by bike or by car for breakfast or lunch and a drink on Fridays, Saturdays or Sundays.

post_content: We are the Warrior Brotherhood MC, Washington State, Chapter B. We are a club of veterans and active duty and reserve service members that enjoy riding motorcycles and working in the community to assist our fellow veterans. We, annually, hold a motorcycle run to benefit Hearts Toward Home International http://www.heartstowardhome.com/ operated by Dr. Bridget Cantrell. Dr. Cantrell has worked with veterans for nearly twenty years helping them work through issues dealing with combat and reintegration. she specializes in PTSD and works directly with deployed troops and their families. She also works specifically with chaplains, military leaders, and military health care providers in helping to recognize signs and symptoms in themselves and their troops as well as provide interventions that can aid them in their journey. She conducts workshops with all branches of service across the country and internationally. She is dedicated to the restoration & reintegration of trauma survivors. She is based in Bellingham, Washington. We have scheduled the run for June 8 this year.
print_desc: Caring for vets and their families. Come enjoy a great ride. Raffling over $7,500 in prizes at the conclusion of the run.
presented_by: Warrior Brotherhood MC, Washington State, Chapter B

post_content: Miles and miles of open road, changing elevations, breath taking scenery with the bluest of blue skies, years of old west and military history await the thundering sounds of two wheel chrome pony’s to explore every inch of the area. Chrome Pony Rally invites you to hit the road and head to its home base, Sierra Vista, Arizona which is approximately 70 miles southeast of Tucson. Sierra Vista is a city of approximately 45,000 at an elevation of 4,600 feet at the foot of the Huachuca (wha-choo-ka) Mountains. With over 300 days of sunshine, you just can’t beat the riding. Within 30 miles in every direction the terrain changes from high desert landscape, to majestic mountains, to rolling prairie fields. At many points you can see for 25 miles in every direction. Open roads are calling!

post_content: One Saturday each month we celebrate the Summer with a free barbecue feast. If you know the kind of parties we throw at Route 65, you won't want to miss this.Each month Lee & Dave prepare a delicious free meal on our giant barbecue rig.  It may be brisket one month, pulled pork the next, and our giant bratwurst and hamburgers the next.  You never know what you are going to get, but you are guaranteed that it is going to be good.  We start serving at 11:30 and go until the food runs out (usually 1:30–2 pm).Other activities at our Super Saturday BBQ vary each month, so keep an eye on Facebook & Twitter or call the shop to get the latest details.

post_content: The Cape Cod & Islands Chapter of the Blue Knights International Law Enforcement Motorcycle Club (MA VI - http://blueknightsma6.tripod.com) announces that its 37th Annual Blessing of the Bikes will be held on Sunday, May 5, 2013 at West Dennis Beach, MA, with the gate opening at 9:30 am. The on-site blessing will occur at noon, so bikes must plan on being there, registered and parked by 11:45 am. The minimum suggested participation donation is $5, with proceeds going to the Blue Knights to be used for charitable purposes; such as our Cape Cod Community College Scholarship, Cape Cod Times Needy Fund, American Cancer Society and Blue Knights Special Fund (assisting fellow Officers involved in motorcycle accidents). Refreshments will be available for purchase and vendors can set-up stands & tables. In past years, up to 1,500 motorcycles traveled from every State in New England to be a part of the Blessing, with an estimated 2,000-2,250 people in attendance.Directions to the Blessing: Take US-6 East to Exit 9A and bear right onto Route 134 South. For a leisurely, scenic ride, take US-6A East to Route 134 South in East Dennis and continue until you pass US-6. Continue 2 miles to the Route 28 traffic lights, then cross Route 28 onto Swan River Road. At the end of Swan River Road, take a right onto Lower County Road and about 3/4 of a mile later take a left onto Lighthouse Road. When you enter the small rotary circle, the Beach entrance is halfway around on the other side of the circle. This entrance will be for motorcycles only; cars should continue around the circle and enter the parking lot to the left of the snack bar.The Blue Knights International Law Enforcement Motorcycle Club was formed in the Spring of 1974 in Bangor, Maine, with the MA VI Chapter being formed at the start of 1976. There are presently over 20,400 members in 637 Chapters located in 25 Countries around the world. The Blue Knights have donated over $16.5 million in cash, goods & services have been donated to more than 1,700 charities, including Concerns of Police Survivors (COPS - Assisting surviving family members of Law Enforcement Officers killed in the line of duty), Cystic Fibrosis, Drug Abuse Resistance Education (DARE), Make-A-Wish, Toys For Tots and many other worthy local charities.
print_desc: The on-site blessing will occur at noon, so bikes must plan on being there, registered and parked by 11:45 am. Refreshments will be available for purchase and vendors can set-up stands and tables.

post_content: Save the Date!!  The 16th Annual Great Teddy Bear Run, Sponsored by the Sarasota H.O.G. (Harley Owners Group) Chapter, is going to be held on Sunday, November, 17th 2013.  This charity event will benefit KIDS by the SEA, a local non-profit, serving children with cancer in our area since 1982.  Every year we have a police escorted parade that starts at The Shoppes at University Center (University Parkway & I-75) with a new teddy bear or other stuffed animal strapped to our Motorcycles and ends at Twin Lakes Park in Sarasota for a big party with lots of food and fun.  For only $15 & a Stuffed Animal for charity, you gain entrance to the parade & event which includes food and a drink.  Beer, Wine, Liquor, Soda & additional Bottled Water will be available for purchase.  Rain or Shine we will still do the event & have a great time!  Once at Twin Lakes Park there will be Raffles, a 50/50 Drawing, Bike Rodeo, Silent Auction & Live Music all day!  This year there will be even more Vendors!  All Bikers, Bike Clubs and the General Public are invited.The public is encouraged to watch the Parade proceed from The Shoppes at University Center, down Honore Ave. to Clark Road, East on Clark to 6700 Clark Road, Twin Lakes Park.  Registration starts at 9:00 AM and ends at 11:15 AM.  We leave in a Police escorted Parade at 11:30 to go to Twin Lakes Park.  Pre-Registration Tickets will be on sale at Rossiter’s Harley-Davidson in Sarasota and Manatee River Harley-Davidson in Bradenton for $10.00 starting September 1st, 2013.  For the first time this year you can purchase your tickets on-line at www.greatteddybearrun.com and pick up your ticket when you arrive at the Teddy Bear Run to turn in your registration form.  This event is open to all bikers and the general public.  Call Sarae with any questions @ 941-951-6103 or e-mail sarae@rossiterharleydavidson.com .  You can get more information at  www.greatteddybearrun.com or  www.facebook.com/16thAnnualGreatTeddyBearRun
print_desc: Rain or shine we will still do the event and have a great time! Once at Twin Lakes Park there will be raffles, a 50/50 drawing, bike rodeo, silent auction and live music all day! This year there will be even more vendors. All bikers, bike clubs and the general public are invited.

post_content: Motorcycle Drag Races in Old Town, Idaho. This event is built around motorcycle drag races right on the street in Old Town, Idaho. It's a unique blast. We are raising money for the Spokane Veterans Forum. At our annual rate of growth, we're expecting between 2,500–3,000 people.Friday is set-up day. We'll build the track (right on the street in Old Town), and if you're a vendor, this is when you'll set up your awning. We'll have over-night security so you can set up and split.Saturday is race day. Anyone can race anything on two or three wheels. Races start early and run all day long. Then, there is a band. This event is like a circus for veterans, bikers and families.Old Town, Idaho, is next to the Pend Oreille River, just east of Newport, Washington. The state border separates the two towns. It's located on Highway 2, about 40 miles north of Spokane and in the midst of gorgeous green mountain roads. The riding in that part of the country is spectacular.
print_desc: Motorcycle street drags and party.
venue: Right on the street in Old Town

post_content: This event is meant to be a celebration of American Heritage, a day long family event which centers around Harley-Davidson, antique cars, new cars, street rods, muscle cars and custom motorcycles. This year is an anniversary for many great American manufacturers; this event will be an opportunity for dealers to display their products. Here are just a few: Harley-Davidson 110th, Chevrolet, and Corvette, Ford, Buick, Chrysler and The Wright Brothers just to name a few. The plan is to bring together the local dealers and any other vendors that would complement each other.Since this is a family event we also have a local game party truck for the kids, Big Foot truck rides, the Bat Mobile and the General Lee Car from the Dukes of Hazard ’60s TV show, two hot air balloons and several other things for the young and old generations. To help support our community we have asked the local fire departments if they want to prepare their specialties and use it as fund raisers. We will have a 40 X 100 food pavilion with chairs and tables. There will also be other food vendors that will include ice cream, funnel cakes, water, soda etc.In conjunction with the FAA which is in our area we were able to have as a guest at our event to celebrate 110 years of the Wright Brothers first fight, NASA astronaut Dr. Terry Hart, who was a mission specialist on STS-41C Challenger (April 6–13, 1984), he will be giving a presentation on his journey.To finish off the evening we will have a band and a grand finale of fire works provided by a local company for entertainment.

post_title: Ride for the Red Motorcycle Run
post_content: The 5th Annual Ride for the Red  90-mile motorcycle run will be hosted by Corning H.O.G. Chapter 3390 on Saturday 8/31/2013 to raise funds for the American Red Cross’ Finger Lakes Region Services to Armed Forces (SAF) Program and local disaster responses.Led by NYS motorcycle Troopers through the beautiful Finger Lakes Region, the ride will depart from Corning Harley-Davidson at 300 Town Center Road in Painted Post, NY. On-site registration runs from 9:00 AM to 11:00 AM; ride leaves at 11:30 AM, immediately following a blessing. Vendors, raffles, live entertainment and more are featured around the event. Contact Corning Harley-Davidson at 607.937.8351 for more information.

post_title: Movie Night: Closer to the Edge
post_content: The Isle of Man Tourist Trophy is the greatest motorcycle road race in the world, the ultimate challenge for rider and machine. It has always called for a commitment far beyond any other racing event, and many have made the ultimate sacrifice in their quest for victory. “Closer to the Edge” is a story about freedom of choice, the strength of human spirit and the will to win. It’s also an examination of what motivates those rare few, this elite band of brothers who risk everything to win the race. See riders push themselves to the limit in this 2011 documentary about the annual Isle of Man TT motorcycle race. Tickets: $5/museum members, $8/non-members

post_title: Peterson's Harley-Davidson's Key West Poker Run

They rumble from Miami to Key West.

post_title: 5th Annual Military Police National Motorcycle Relay Ride
post_content: The Military Police National Motorcycle Relay Ride (MPNMRR) is a Canadian coast-to-coast charity event that is raising funds in support of the Military Police Fund for Blind Children and the Children's Wish Foundation. The MPNMRR is the longest annual motorcycle relay in the world with our National Riders covering in excess of 10,000 kilometers during the event.Join the 5th Annual Military Police National Motorcycle Relay Ride, as it rolls through your area between August 2 and 25. All motorcycle enthusiasts are welcome to participate, whether it is as a national, provincial or local rider. On August 2, the 5th Annual MPNMRR kicks off on “The Rock” where motorcycle enthusiasts will roll their throttles out of St. John’s, NL and will visit all of the major military establishments across Canada, arriving in beautiful Victoria, BC on August 25. Courageous riders will even venture south from the frigid temperatures of the Northwest Territories to meet riders in Alberta, riding a whopping 3459 kilometers! Over the past 4 years, the MPNMRR has raised over $170,000 for several charities.The Military Police Fund for Blind Children is a registered charitable organization that specializes in assisting visually impaired children and young adults up to the age of 21 in our local communities. The fund is operated entirely by Military Police volunteers and has no paid employees. Funding is prioritized for educational aids such as computers, software and accessories, Spinoza bears, visually stimulating books, electronics, learning aids, activity panels, guide dogs, attendance at specialized institutions (which can include tuition), and summer camps.

post_title: Prairie Material's 3rd Annual Run For the Vet's
post_content: Prairie Material's 3rd annual run for the Vets will take place on Sunday, September 8, 2013. All proceeds will go directly to the Manteno Veterans home located in Manteno, Illinois. This is a 50 mile escorted run. A POW/MIA concrete mixer will be the lead vehicle this year. For a $10 per person entry fee you will get an event shirt, coffee and donuts, a cookout at the end of the run that includes burgers and brats along with soft drinks. All Veteran's living at the home will be served before the run people. We have raised in excess of $12,000 in the last three years in cash and supplies for our Veterans that live at the home. Run line up will start at 8 am with kickstands up at 10 am. Bikes, hot rods and regular vehicles are all invited to join in.

post_title: The 16th Annual Chester Norman Thomas Motorcycle Ride to benefit David’s House
post_content: There will be a catered lunch provided at the end site at David’s House in Lebanon, New Hampshire. There will also be a Chinese raffle with lots of great prizes. Raffle tickets are $1 each or six tickets for $5. This year’s honoree is Eric Adams, 11, who is bravely facing Burkett’s Lymphoma Leukemia. This event will be a guided ride to David’s House provided by the Monadnock Harley Owner’s Group (H.O.G.) with assistance from various law enforcement agencies providing additional traffic assistance. This event is open to all types of motorcycles.All monies raised by the Benefit Ride will go directly to support the mission of David’s House. David's House provides a home-away-from-home and support for families with children receiving treatment through Children's Hospital at Dartmouth-Hitchcock Medical Center in Lebanon, NH. Since opening its doors in 1986, David's House has served over 12,000 families from around the world.David's House is located on Mount Support Road on the campus of Dartmouth-Hitchcock Medical Center in Lebanon, NH. It is a pleasant half-mile walk from the Medical CenterDavid's House is the dream of a young boy named David Cyr, who passed away from leukemia in 1984 at the age of five. For three and a half years, David was treated at Mary Hitchcock Memorial Hospital in Hanover, NH. Visiting David during his hospitalizations was easy for his parents who lived only 20 minutes away. But during this time his family met others who didn't have that option; instead they slept in their cars, in the waiting room, or in a chair at bedside to be close to their child. When David's doctor told the Cyrs that David had just months to live, his father, Dick, asked the doctor, "Why isn't there a place for families like ours to stay?" The doctor told him there had been talk about a house in this area, but nothing had ever come of it. Dick replied, "We're going to build a place, and we're going to call it David's House." One week after David passed away, his parents and their friends began raising funds for David's House. The first money was David's own: $300.78 in birthday money and his dad's spare change that David had stashed away throughout the house. Whenever Dick asked him what he was saving for, David always replied, "For a special reason, Dad." That special reason has now served over 12,000 families from around the world!

This event is open to all types of motorcycles.All monies raised by the Benefit Ride will go directly to support the mission of David’s House. post_title: But I Have Diabetes Annual Poker Run
post_content: On December 7th, 2011 our daughter Madison was diagnosed with Type 1 Diabetes, at just 5 years old. Her diagnosis has affected our family deeply. Our pain and grief at the loss of her freedom as a child has inspired us to raise awareness about a growing epidemic affecting young children all over. In order to help our family and other families cope, and to have a place to reach out for support we have decided to become proactive with our daughter's disease. Young children diagnosed with this disease are subjected to as many as 10 finger pokes a day and possibly up to as many as 8 insulin shots a day to maintain their health. Diabetes is not just a strain on these children but also on their siblings, parents, and caregivers."But I have Diabetes" is a non-profit organization: Our goal is to grow by creating a charitable giving campaign to promote diabetes awareness. Support newly affected families by providing them with information about their new diagnosis and with the support of other families that have been affected by this disease for many years. Provide children and their families with the supplies, and support they wouldn't normally be able to afford. Creating support groups for children and their families to share experiences trials and tribulations that they have had while they fight this disease.We are hosting our 2nd annual motorcycle run July 27th 2013, which will include the following: a barbecue, raffle drawings, education & Information booth, live music and much more. Our goal for this event is to raise money to help children and families with Diabetes. Part of the proceeds will also be going to JDRF (Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation) jdrfbayarea.org. JDRF is the leader of the type 1 diabetes (T1D) community—unifying global efforts to cure, treat, and prevent T1D.
